hard drive question ok my motherboard took a crap on me and i have a lot of stuff i don't want to lose and that can't be replaced i've since bought a new computer and i guess my question is is there any way i can get those files from my old hard drive and get them into my new computer i'd appreciate any help you guys can give me my old computer is an emachine w xp and my new one is a dell with xp my bet is that your old emachine had a pata ide hard disk drive and your new dell has an sata hard disk drive and doesn't have an extra connection for your old hard drive on the cd rom cable the easiest thing to do is remove your hard drive from your emachine and go buy you one of these usb to ide sata cables http www tigerdirect com applications searchtools item details asp edpno sku v srccode googlebase cmp otc googlebase you can also go out and buy you an external enclosure like this one http www tigerdirect com applications searchtools item details asp edpno catid then just hook the drives up properly and connect the usb cable to your new computer then you can browse the hard drive good luck hth Hard disk Serial ATA Universal Serial Bus Floppy disk USB flash drive Redundant array of independent disks AmigaOS IMac Computer bus Windows XP Timeline of computing 1990-forward SCSI Power Macintosh G3 Apple IIGS Linux IPod Apple II family Atari ST BIOS Mouse (computing) Amiga Computer forensics Apple Macintosh MicroATX Commodore International Symbian OS Atari 8-bit family FreeDOS Digital photography Commodore 64 Sega Mega Drive/Sega Genesis IBM PC Flash memory Common Unix Printing System USB mass storage device class ZX Spectrum Shit Sound Blaster Personal computer Visual Basic Web server Sound card Macintosh Finder DVD Xbox File system PlayStation 2 Xserve Modchip Spyware Copy protection IBM Personal System/2 World Wide Web Mac OS X v10.4 IBM PC compatible Disk cloning Bluetooth Digital audio player Knoppix Laptop Southbridge (computing) Amstrad CPC Virtual memory RS-232 IBoo